Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.96,0:02:20.14,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:134968,140140}However, Maya could not celebrate:\NThoughts of her mother filled her mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.72,0:02:28.10,Episode title,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:140724,148106}{\an5\pos(766,720)\fscy95\blur1\fad(800,0)}—Episode 16—\NTrace of Mother
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.10,0:02:30.10,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:148106,150108}Dear mother.\NHow are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.06,0:02:32.56,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:149066,152569}Today is the last day\Nof "The Smile of Stone".
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.90,0:02:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:155906,158617}What are you doing, Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.61,0:02:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:158617,160661}We only have an hour left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.66,0:02:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:160661,162788}You know you'll be scolded\Nif you're late, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.16,0:02:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:164164,167584}You can take all your time\Ntomorrow to write that letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.58,0:02:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:167584,170420}It's not like your mom's\Ngoing anywhere. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.75,0:02:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:171755,172923}Maya, hurry, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.92,0:02:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:172923,174549}Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.80,0:03:03.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:180806,183266}I'm sorry, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.26,0:03:07.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:183266,187187}It's been two years, but I haven't\Neven written a single letter to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.18,0:03:09.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:187187,189189}You don't even know that\Nwe went out of business,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.18,0:03:11.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:189189,191983}or that I moved into an apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.98,0:03:14.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:191983,194236}I haven't even told you\Nabout all the acting I've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.03,0:03:18.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:197030,198949}Today's our final performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.94,0:03:22.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:198948,202411}I wish you had a chance to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.74,0:03:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:204746,205997}Mother…?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.37,0:03:29.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:207374,209000}No, that can't be…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.42,0:03:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:216425,217843}Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.80,0:03:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:219803,221930}Mom!\NThat's my mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.93,0:03:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:221930,223765}Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.76,0:03:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:223765,226393}Please let me off here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.39,0:03:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:226393,228478}Please let me off!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.47,0:03:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:228478,230147}What's going on with you, Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.14,0:03:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:230147,232315}My mother.\NThat was my mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.44,0:03:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:237446,239740}She was right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.78,0:04:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:243785,246413}Maya, are you sure\Nyou weren't seeing things?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.20,0:04:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:251209,252377}Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.46,0:04:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:256465,257924}Mother, wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.97,0:04:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:268977,269936}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.27,0:04:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:271271,274274}You'll be late for the play, Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.27,0:04:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:274274,275609}Our play…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.60,0:04:39.11,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:275609,279112}The Smile of Stone
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.65,0:04:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:276651,278570}Hey, did you see our audience today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.57,0:04:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:278570,280322}Orion Theatre's actors are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.32,0:04:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:280322,284075}I see. Their production\Nof "Hamlet" finished yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.07,0:04:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:284075,285702}Miss Tsukikage is here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.33,0:04:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:288330,291082}Okay, guys.\NLet's do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.08,0:04:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:291082,292375}Hmm, where's Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.47,0:05:07.47,Sign,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:304471,307474}Manpuku Ken
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.76,0:05:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:305764,308225}Where's Haru?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.22,0:05:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:308225,310602}That's what I want to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.60,0:05:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:310602,314147}I thought she went to visit you, Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.14,0:05:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:314147,318652}She disappeared on her way to a\Nnursing home, we haven't heard from her since.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.65,0:05:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:318652,320362}Nursing home?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.36,0:05:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:320362,323657}Was it her lungs?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.65,0:05:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:323657,325784}Yes. For a long time,\Nshe was just lying in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.78,0:05:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:325784,329371}We wanted to let you know,\Nbut we couldn't get in touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.37,0:05:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:329371,331665}So, we had to make a—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:331665,334376}Maya, it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.12,0:05:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:332123,334376}{\an8}Hello? Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.37,0:05:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:334376,337254}Thank you.\NI'll have to call you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.96,0:05:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:337963,341716}So, you have to at least\Ntell us your address—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.71,0:05:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:341716,343677}Hello, Maya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.67,0:05:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:343677,344719}Oh, she's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.26,0:05:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:345262,348640}Maya has been doing\Na great job all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.64,0:05:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:348640,352185}And we should expect nothing less of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.18,0:05:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:352185,357482}The success of this play hinges on\NMaya's portrayal of that doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.36,0:06:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:362362,365699}I will be watching you carefully, Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.69,0:06:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:365699,366950}Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.36,0:06:12.78,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:368368,372789}"The Smile of Stone's"\Nlast day had come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.78,0:06:15.83,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:372789,375834}The joint production\Nby Tsukikage and Ikkakuju Theatres
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.83,0:06:22.71,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:375834,382716}brought the old converted cafe to life,\Nand the audience watched intently.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.63,0:06:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:383633,385176}That's Kitajima Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.80,0:06:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:385802,394853}I would like to declare a qualified contributor\Nwho will take care of the doll Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.85,0:06:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:394853,396271}A contributor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.27,0:06:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:396271,403403}Yes, the person must honestly\Nlove and care about Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.40,0:06:48.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:403403,408408}If she's been missing…\NThen that must have been my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.40,0:06:51.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:408408,411328}Tuberculosis…\NThat's why she was so thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.75,0:06:59.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:416750,419002}I'm sorry, so sorry, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.00,0:07:01.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:419002,421379}For not being able to take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.42,0:07:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:423423,427844}So, Ms. Isabella, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.67,0:07:13.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:429679,433516}I'm the only one she has…\Nthe only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.80,0:07:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:433808,434434}Hey…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.43,0:07:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:434434,435936}Look at that…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.64,0:07:17.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:436645,437479}Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:27.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:443985,447989}The mask is gone,\Nshe's no longer a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.86,0:07:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:450867,454371}Shoot, the important doll\Nis all soaking wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.53,0:07:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:456539,459918}Hanna, please help me\Nchange Elizabeth's outfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.13,0:07:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:464130,467467}Frederica, when did you start\Nplaying with your dolls as a hobby?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:467467,471304}Oh, Mr. Gallison,\Nwhat's with you and your duster?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.26,0:07:56.26,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:472263,476267}The water hid Maya's tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.26,0:08:04.69,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:476267,484693}The play went on as if nothing happened,\NRei's wit had saved the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.44,0:08:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:491449,494035}What was that…?\NI felt drawn in, or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.03,0:08:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:494035,498331}Yeah, I was sucked in by\Nsome kind of… passion, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:498331,502502}They were all skilled actors.\NEspecially that doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.08,0:08:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:503086,506715}Maybe she's a good find.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.75,0:08:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:509759,514931}What were you thinking,\Ntaking your mask off on stage?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.51,0:08:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:515515,518351}Because of your unprofessional behavior,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.35,0:08:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:518351,522480}our all-important finale\Nwas almost irreversibly ruined.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.48,0:08:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:522480,527068}Miss Tsukikage, earlier today Maya saw someone\Nthat seemed like her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.40,0:08:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:528403,532615}The reason matters not,\Nremoving your mask on stage is unacceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.61,0:08:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:532615,535201}Maya… you have failed as an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.20,0:08:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:536202,537912}Failed?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.91,0:08:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:537912,539998}You will not be in our next play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.99,0:09:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:539998,542250}As of now, you are on probation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.33,0:09:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:545336,546838}Probation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.83,0:09:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:546838,551342}I should have killed my emotions\Nbefore I went on stage…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.34,0:09:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:551342,553136}You couldn't help it, Maya.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.13,0:09:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:553136,557015}What we wear is a glass mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.01,0:09:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:557015,558433}Glass mask?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.43,0:09:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:558433,561770}Yes.\NA fragile glass mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.77,0:09:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:561770,565774}That's why it's so easy to break it\Nand reveal our true selves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.77,0:09:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:565774,572572}You can tell an actor's skill\Nby their ability to keep the mask on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.74,0:09:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:578745,580914}A glass mask…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.21,0:09:50.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:587212,590215}I took the mask off on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.21,0:09:54.34,Retrospective,,0,0,0,,{TIME:590215,594344}If you fail, "The Crimson Goddess"\Nwill go to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.34,0:09:55.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:594344,595553}It's over for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.55,0:09:57.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:595553,597555}Miss Tsukikage must have given up on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.55,0:09:59.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:597555,599891}I'll never be\N"The Crimson Goddess" now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.89,0:10:03.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:599891,603436}Did I reject my mother's concerns and\Npush her out of my life, all for nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.43,0:10:06.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:603436,606231}Mother… Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.11,0:10:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:618118,620620}Maya, can you stop the alarm?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.99,0:10:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:621996,623622}Hey, Maya!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.46,0:10:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:628461,629462}Oh, where'd she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.39,0:10:49.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:646396,649274}Mother… I want to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.27,0:10:52.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:649274,652694}I want to bury my face in your chest\Nand be your daughter again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.86,0:11:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:660869,664122}These are the candidates\Nfor Helen Keller.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.12,0:11:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:664122,666541}There are about 15 candidates.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.66,0:11:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:667667,670920}Thanks for all your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.92,0:11:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:670920,672797}This one is a provisional nominee.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.79,0:11:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:672797,675216}Hmm, provisional?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.21,0:11:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:675216,679888}Yes. I haven't seen how she moves or speaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.88,0:11:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:679888,682473}She played a doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.47,0:11:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:682473,688021}But I saw her talent shine through,\Nwithout a single motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.02,0:11:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:688021,690231}Very well, we will\Ngive her our consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.23,0:11:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:690231,691064}Certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.52,0:11:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:692525,693484}Haseagawa…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.48,0:11:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:693484,694777}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.07,0:11:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:696070,698573}How did you become\Nsuch a great scout?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.57,0:11:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:698573,699532}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.53,0:11:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:699532,701326}Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.17,0:11:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:712170,715215}Where the heck did Maya go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.21,0:11:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:715215,717007}Oh, that must be her.
Comment: 0,0:12:05.72,0:12:05.72,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:725725,725725}Eyecatch
Comment: 0,0:12:09.47,0:12:09.47,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:729479,729479}#Eyecatch
Comment: 0,0:12:12.39,0:12:12.39,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:732398,732398}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.35,0:12:18.19,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:733358,738196}For three days, Maya searched for her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.57,0:12:26.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:741574,746704}She might not be in Tōkyō anymore…\NWhere did she go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.70,0:12:28.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:746704,748081}Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.66,0:12:31.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:749666,751125}"The Cherry Tree\Nof Dream Festivals".
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.12,0:12:34.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:751125,754295}That's the one where Himekawa Ayumi\Nplays a daughter of a wealthy family.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.34,0:12:43.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:758341,763429}Ayumi is looking fabulous on stage, and look\Nat me: I'm on probation and losing my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.42,0:12:47.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:763429,767350}Maybe I'll never become an actress,\Nmaybe I've failed…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.98,0:12:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:771980,775108}Thank you so much for your visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.10,0:12:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:775108,778611}The actors were really happy\Nthat you visited, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.61,0:13:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:778611,781531}I heard Himekawa Ayumi is doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.53,0:13:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:781531,784659}She was born to play the main role.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.65,0:13:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:784659,786452}I'm looking forward to her future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.45,0:13:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:786452,790665}Mr. Ōta! Kawamura Yoshiko\Nfell off the stairs and broke her leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.66,0:13:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:790665,793835}W-What!?\NThen make her walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.83,0:13:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:793835,795962}There's no one else for her part.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.96,0:13:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:795962,801175}But it's all swollen\Nand she can't even move it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.17,0:13:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:801175,803970}Damn, we've got no choice.\NWe'll have to change the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.97,0:13:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:803970,806180}Call Mr. Isomura, the playwright.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.18,0:13:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:806180,808224}No, there's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.97,0:13:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:811978,813438}Mr. Masumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.07,0:13:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:821070,824615}Is this your shelter\Nfrom the rain, little girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.61,0:13:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:824615,826826}You again…?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.82,0:13:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:826826,828077}Leave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.07,0:13:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:828077,829537}I can't let you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.53,0:13:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:829537,832665}You are our important substitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.66,0:13:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:832665,834709}A substitute?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.70,0:13:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:834709,839213}Mr. Ōta, could you tell her\Nwhat the play is about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.21,0:14:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:839213,841966}But, we only have another hour\Nbefore our play starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.96,0:14:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:841966,843885}It's impossible for her\Nto get the words memorized.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.88,0:14:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:843885,846512}It's okay.\NHere, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.51,0:14:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:846512,850767}Wait a minute.\NI haven't agreed to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.76,0:14:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:850767,852101}You will do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.64,0:14:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:853644,859067}Or are you so stubborn that you will\Ndiscard every opportunity I give you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.69,0:14:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:861694,867200}Besides, this is a very well-known production.\NYour only fan might be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.40,0:14:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:868409,870411}Mr. Purple Rose!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.41,0:14:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:870411,871829}Here, get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.49,0:14:36.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:874499,876584}I will never like this guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.96,0:14:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:881964,886302}Please memorize your lines quickly.\NWe don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.30,0:14:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:886302,887220}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.76,0:14:56.56,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:894769,896562}Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:14:58.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:896562,898815}Kitajima Maya!?\NWhy is she here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.81,0:15:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:898815,903444}Everyone, let me introduce Kitajima Maya.\NShe will act as Chie's substitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.49,0:15:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:907490,909867}Ayumi, she will play\Nas your cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.95,0:15:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:910952,912370}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.37,0:15:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:912370,916124}Cousin?\NI'll be her cousin?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.12,0:15:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:916124,919252}Yes. Under a very peculiar circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.29,0:15:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:920294,923673}This is our first play together.\NLet's do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.30,0:15:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:933307,937770}Sorry we couldn't find you a better place,\Nbut we're counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.77,0:15:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:937770,941649}Your appear in the third and fourth scene\Nof the first act, and the fifth in the second act.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.64,0:15:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:941649,945069}It starts at 6 PM.\NBreak a leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.69,0:15:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:948698,950950}I only have 45 more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.00,0:16:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:964005,968092}So that's the girl\NMiss Harada called the "Stage Storm".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.09,0:16:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:968092,971929}I heard she tied with Himekawa Ayumi\Nin the amateur contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.92,0:16:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:971929,974599}But, so what?\NShe just doesn't have enough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.59,0:16:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:974599,977477}It's not like she only has\Nto remember her part.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.73,0:16:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:984734,986651}What's wrong with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.65,0:16:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:986651,988905}Can't she hear the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.90,0:16:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:988905,991616}Look at her concentration.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.96,0:16:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1002960,1007048}We've really got the worst luck.\NShe'll be on stage with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.04,0:16:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1007048,1011052}The "Stage Storm"…\NShe might overwhelm us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.05,0:16:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1011052,1012887}And we'd finally gotten major roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.88,0:16:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1012887,1016140}I hope she forgets her words\Nand falls silent or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.14,0:16:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1016140,1017141}I know…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.14,0:16:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1017141,1018476}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.47,0:17:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1018476,1020603}I have a good idea, Bungo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.68,0:17:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1021687,1023689}T-That's a little too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.68,0:17:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1023689,1027568}Hmph.\NIt's eat or be eaten in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.32,0:17:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1032323,1034367}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.36,0:17:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1034367,1038204}Why don't you change\Nand do your makeup now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.20,0:17:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1038204,1041040}But I have only gotten\Nto the third scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.04,0:17:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1041040,1046754}You can read even after the play has started.\NYou don't appear until the third scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.75,0:17:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1046754,1048339}Well, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.33,0:17:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1048339,1051801}Here, hurry.\NI can help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.80,0:17:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1051801,1053302}This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.51,0:17:43.06,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1057515,1063062}The script Bungo had was the original one,\Nuntouched by the playwright's edits.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.06,0:17:50.31,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1063062,1070319}Isomura had drastically changed the fourth scene-\Nnot only the words, but also the storyline.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.31,0:17:53.65,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1070319,1073656}The play is set in the Meiji Era,\Nwhen the Rokumeikan was in its heyday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.65,0:17:56.90,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1073656,1076909}This is a drama about\NKaizōji, a baron, and his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.74,0:18:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1077743,1080538}Uncle, Aunt.\NLook at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.53,0:18:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1080538,1085459}Ms. Barnette, my tutor, taught me\Nhow to greet in the Western way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.16,0:18:10.17,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1086168,1090172}Ayumi's role is a baron's\Nproud granddaughter, Tsukiyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.17,0:18:13.80,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1090172,1093801}Maya's role is a daughter born\Nto his fifth son, Yukihiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.80,0:18:17.76,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1093801,1097763}As a geisha, she grew up\Nwithout any privilege.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.76,0:18:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1097763,1100099}I've finally learned my lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.09,0:18:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1100099,1103519}Now I need to learn\Nhow to portray Chie in my own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.51,0:18:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1103519,1105146}What a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.14,0:18:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1105146,1107398}She has memorized\Nall the words already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.39,0:18:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1107398,1111360}Well, too bad.\NYour words will be useless on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.90,0:18:34.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1112903,1114655}Mr. Purple Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.65,0:18:36.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1114655,1116741}Please watch me tonight\Nif you are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.74,0:18:39.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1116741,1119160}I will show you my Chie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1124749,1128836}You weren't back at the promised time,\Nso I came to pick you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.83,0:18:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1128836,1132757}I put her in as a substitute,\Nso I must take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.75,0:18:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1132757,1137094}I knew you would say that, so I\Ncanceled all your appointments.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.09,0:18:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1137094,1138638}Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.43,0:19:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1139430,1142933}How was the meeting between\NTsukiyo and Mr. Funakura?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.93,0:19:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1142933,1144727}It went acceptably well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.56,0:19:09.48,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1145561,1149482}The third scene of the first act went smoothly,\Nand the fourth was about to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.44,0:19:11.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1150441,1151651}I'm on next.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.65,0:19:14.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1151651,1154945}Yukihiro, my father,\Nwill come back soon, and—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.94,0:19:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1154945,1157073}Bad news about Mr. Yukihiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.07,0:19:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1157073,1158949}What about Yukihiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.66,0:19:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1160660,1162870}He went off to be an entertainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.41,0:19:24.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1163412,1164413}It's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.41,0:19:26.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1164413,1166123}This is different\Nfrom what I've read!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.21,0:19:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1170211,1171379}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.09,0:19:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1174090,1176008}This is all wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.00,0:19:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1176008,1178552}The father was supposed to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.17,0:19:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1179178,1180513}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.84,0:19:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1181847,1183724}Oh, this is the old script.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.01,0:19:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1186018,1188688}Uncle Yukihiro\Nbecame an entertainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.68,0:19:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1188688,1191565}How embarrassing.\NI wonder if Chie knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.56,0:19:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1191565,1192858}Chie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.85,0:19:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1192858,1193984}How did this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.98,0:19:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1193984,1195361}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.36,0:19:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1195361,1196070}Chie!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.27,0:19:59.24,Thought,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1197279,1199240}They're calling me.\NI have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.90,0:20:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1200908,1203494}What are you doing, little girl?\NStop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.08,0:20:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1206080,1207915}No, Mr. Masumi!\NThe play is on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.83,0:20:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1211836,1213796}She came out.\NWhat nerve.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.96,0:20:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1215965,1219427}Chie, your father\Nis an embarrassment to our family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.42,0:20:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1219427,1221345}And so are you, Chie.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.34,0:20:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1221345,1223139}Why don't you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.13,0:20:25.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1223139,1225182}Say something, but what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.05,0:20:32.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1227059,1232189}Chie is supposed to have a long speech\Nabout her sad and miserable life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.18,0:20:34.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1232189,1234108}I wonder what she will do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.65,0:20:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1242658,1244493}Say something!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.51,0:21:07.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1266515,1267892}What a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.89,0:21:09.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1267892,1269977}Not only has she avoided having to speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.97,0:21:14.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1269977,1274356}but by biting on the lily,\Nshe expressed her sorrow and bitterness.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.03,0:21:26.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1283032,1286577}What should I do?\NHow should I react to this Chie?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.57,0:21:28.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1286577,1288746}I can't get the play going…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.74,0:21:30.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1288746,1290122}How stupid are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.12,0:21:32.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1290122,1292416}They fell into their own trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.46,0:21:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1295461,1298047}Ayumi, it's not your turn yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.00,0:21:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1301008,1304970}Mr. Utahiko, Ms. Kyoko,\Nyour mother is calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.72,0:21:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1305721,1306430}Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.43,0:21:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1306430,1307264}Right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.43,0:21:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1308432,1311476}She made those two get off the stage…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.47,0:21:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1311476,1313521}Where is this play going?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.32,0:22:02.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1321320,1322321}Ayumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.78,0:22:07.11,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1324782,1327117}Kitajima Maya…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.11,0:22:10.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1327117,1330746}I never thought our battle would be like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.46,0:22:27.01,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1340464,1347012}Maya, who came out on the stage\Nwithout even knowing the storyline.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.01,0:22:30.97,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1347012,1350975}Ayumi, who came out on the stage\Nwhen it wasn't even her turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.97,0:22:37.64,Narrator,(narrator),0,0,0,,{TIME:1350975,1357648}It was as if time stopped\Nas the two girls stared at each other.
